b'Equipment Lending Policy'
b'Overview\xc2\xa0'
b'The ACCC\xc2\xa0provides multimedia equipment for a variety of uses:'
b'Event Support (Audio/Visual) service page'
b'Features\xc2\xa0'
b'Students:'
b'Students are able to check out equipment/accessories from three locations on campus:'
b'The checkout duration for students is three business days, and a checkout can be renewed one time for an additional three days, but the student must physically return to the checkout location with the equipment to renew the checkout.\xc2\xa0 Equipment checkouts to students are first-come, first-serve, there are no reservations.'
b'Faculty:'
b'In-Class Use:'
b'Faculty/Instructors are able to check out equipment for use in a particular class session.\xc2\xa0 Checkouts are made for the duration of a class session and must be returned promptly to be available for other instructors.\xc2\xa0 Equipment can be checked out from the LTS Support office at Lecture Center E, room E112 (west side of the building).\xc2\xa0 The following equipment is available for this type of checkout:'
b'Larger equipment such as the TV monitors can be delivered and setup in the classroom.\xc2\xa0 High-value items such as laptops and projectors *must* be checked out in person from the office.\xc2\xa0 Instructors are able to designate a Teaching Assistant to pick up equipment in their stead.'
b'Multiple-Day Use:'
b'Faculty/Instructors are able to check out multimedia equipment for the purpose of multimedia development, from the ACCC-LTS Multimedia Lab, located in the Daley Library room 1-030 (formerly the Instructional Technology Lab East).\xc2\xa0 Checkouts are for three business days.\xc2\xa0 The following equipment is available at this location:'
b'Applicability\xc2\xa0'
b'In order to check out equipment from the ACCC, you must be a current student, faculty, or staff member. \xc2\xa0All lending of equipment is subject to the Equipment Lending Policy.'
b'Equipment Lending Policy'
b'Cost\xc2\xa0'
b'There are no up-front costs associated with checkout of equipment to students or faculty. \xc2\xa0However, fines may be incurred per the Equipment Lending Policy.'
b'Equipment Lending Policy'
b'There are rental fees associated with checkout of equipment for scheduled events. \xc2\xa0These costs are detailed at the Event Support (Audio/Visual) service page.'
b'Event Support (Audio/Visual) service page'
b'Support\xc2\xa0'
b'\xc2\xa0'
b'\xc2\xa0'
b'LTS@uic.edu'
b'Further Information\xc2\xa0'
b'ACCC Service Level Agreement (SLA)'
b'Immediate checkout at equipment lending locations. Reservations for faculty require 2 business days\xc2\xa0notice.'
b'Under 2 business days.'
b'Based on hours of operation at lending locations (between 8:00am -\xc2\xa07:00pm in\xc2\xa0some locations and\xc2\xa09:00am - 5:00pm in others). Not available during Academic Calendar break periods.'
